{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019Jcy2FyqTSEKT7GyJEMBNv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All Phase B HTTP checks pass:\n- GET `/test` contains `Live` ✅ (also contains `Disconnected`)\n- GET `/test` contains `Pause` ✅ \n- GET `/test` contains `Clear` ✅\n\nNow let me review the test coverage more carefully to see if there are any integration tests I should write.\n\nThe plan has an \"Integration gap\" note:\n- HTTP checks for `/test` page rendering — requires dev server\n\nI've verified these manually. Since the plan doesn't mention any Playwright e2e tests (and the plan doesn't require them for F28 specifically), and the HTTP checks are covered, I need to decide whether to write additional tests.\n\n\nThe integration gap mentioned in the plan is just the HTTP checks, which I've now confirmed are working. The hook and component tests already cover the spec behaviors and UI rendering, so I think I have sufficient coverage to write the eval file now.\n\nLooking at the test counts, I have 13 tests each in the hook and component test files. Let me verify the prepend behavior is properly tested — specifically that newer events appear at the top of the list.\n\nThe max 200 events limit and pause/resume functionality both check out, and the connection status indicator correctly toggles between green and red based on the connection state. Everything aligns with the spec requirements.\n\nBefore finalizing the eval, I should note that while the component tests mock the hook, the hook tests themselves directly verify the SSE behavior, so the critical functionality is covered.\n\nOne gap I'm noticing: there's no test confirming the 200-event cap applies when flushing buffered events on resume, though the implementation itself handles this correctly by merging and slicing the combined array.\n\nSince the code path is straightforward and the instructions discourage testing trivially obvious behavior